      • getSuperClassSubstitutor

        public static PsiSubstitutor getSuperClassSubstitutor(PsiClass superClass,
                                                      PsiClass derivedClass,
                                                      PsiSubstitutor derivedSubstitutor)
        Calculates substitutor that binds type parameters in superClass with values that they have in derivedClass, given that type parameters in derivedClass are bound by derivedSubstitutor. superClass must be a super class/interface of derivedClass (as in InheritanceUtil.isInheritorOrSelf(derivedClass, superClass, true)
        Returns:
        substitutor (never returns null)
        See Also:
        PsiClass.isInheritor(PsiClass, boolean), InheritanceUtil.isInheritorOrSelf(PsiClass, PsiClass, boolean)

      • isSafeConversion

        public static boolean isSafeConversion(PsiType target,
                                       PsiType source)
        Returns true if numeric conversion (widening or narrowing) does not lose the information. This differs slightly from isAssignable(PsiType, PsiType) result as some assignable types still may lose the information. E.g. double doubleVar = longVar may lose round the long value.
        Parameters:
        target - target type
        source - source type
        Returns:
        true if numeric conversion (widening or narrowing) does not lose the information.
